author: Odeinoichus
title: 7.50 an hour, and all the food I can eat.
review:
Set #71013 Babysitter: It's a LEGO Baby, it's the first LEGO Baby, what more can we say? It's definitely one we want to see more of, but for now just get as many of her as you can find.

With dual-molded arms for a short-sleeve look and a double sided torso print this Minifigure has no other detailing, there's no printing for her legs. Her hair is the same as the Zombie Cheerleader, perhaps this is what she looked like before being bitten. Her accessory is of course a baby bottle and a LEGO Baby, yep she's got a little baby to take care of which means you get two minifigs for the price of one in this set.

I would strongly suggest buying multiples, while her shirt design is a bit goofy looking, the parts alone and the baby are definitley well worth the asking price for this pack.
